            . I am a <rs id="t18220911-187-viclabel984" type="occupation">dyer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220911-187-victim1802 t18220911-187-viclabel984"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18220911-187-crimeloc985">Craven-place, Bayswater</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18220911-187-crimeloc985" type="placeName" value="Craven-place, Bayswater"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18220911-187-crimeloc985" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220911-187-off982 t18220911-187-crimeloc985"></join>. I hung a pair of trowsers to dry on the bannisters all night, and next afternoon about one I came from town; the prisoner, (whose sister lodged up stairs,) went up, and after he came down I was going to take them down, and missed them; I went out and found them on his barrow in a wrapper; I met him coming along with some gin, called him, and asked if he was not ashamed of himself, he said it was the first time he ever did such a thing; I gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220911-187-person1804">
                  THOMAS 
                  CROW
               <interp inst="t18220911-187-person1804" type="surname" value="CROW"></interp>
